-- Polish Stocks: PBG, KGHM Polska Miedz, TVN Shares Move in Warsaw
-- B y   K a t y a   A n d r u s z
-- 2011-12-27T17:04:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-27/polish-stocks-pbg-kghm-polska-miedz-tvn-shares-move-in-warsaw.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  gained 4.52, or
0.2 percent, to 2,173.35 at the close of trading in Warsaw,
trimming this year’s decline to 21 percent.  The following were among the active equities on the Warsaw
Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  KGHM Polska Miedz SA (KGH)  , the copper producer with the
biggest European mine output, lost 2 percent to 112.7 zloty. The
company may seek further acquisitions if it succeeds in its
planned purchase of Canada’s Quadra FNX Mining Ltd., Dziennik
reported today, citing Chief Executive Office Herbert Wirth.  PBG SA (PBG)  , Poland’s third-largest construction
company, jumped 3.6 percent to 72.3 zloty, extending gains after
rising as much as 5.8 percent on Dec. 23. The company received a
first-time corporate family rating of B2 with a “stable”
outlook from Moody’s Investors Services on Dec. 22.  TVN SA (TVN)  , the country’s largest television station,
fell 1 percent to 10.2 zloty. The shares had rallied 13.6
percent last week after Vivendi SA’s Canal Plus agreed to pay
230 million euros ($301 million) for a 40 percent stake in N-
Vision BV, the owner of TVN SA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katya Andrusz in Warsaw at 
